Nocona High School
August 22 at 1:42 PM ·

We'd like to thank everyone for the rush of NEW subscribers to our NHS Digital Media youtube channel. Subscribing is a great way to keep up with ALL things video at NHS. However, there is some confusion out there about our ability to livestream the home football games without 1,000 subscribers. We can and will livestream those games to youtube because we are doing that from computer just like we did NHS Graduation 2020.

Youtube only requires 1,000 subscribers to livestream through a mobile device like an iPad or iPhone like we plan to use for Varsity Volleyball home games. We have decided to livestream the volleyball games through Facebook Live from the Nocona Indian & Lady Indian Athletics facebook page. Nocona ISD Athletics

I hope this clears up any concerns or confusion about our sports livestreams this year. As always, we appreciate everyone's support.....GO INDIANS!!!

Nocona High School
July 21 at 8:17 AM ·

The school start date has been adjusted to allow NISD more time to prepare for the challenging circumstances of 2020-2021. School will now start on Tuesday, August 18th. We will be offering a face-to-face option as well as a remote option.

There is more information still coming from the state (TEA and UIL). With that, we are learning what we can do and making decisions on what is best for our students and teachers in Nocona with that information.

Be looking for more information as we get closer to the start of school.

We are excited to have students back in the building! A school building is a sad building with no students in it.

Nocona ISD Athletics
July 11 at 12:50 PM ·

When we resume workouts on July 13th, the boys schedule will change:
Mondays will be in the evening 7:00-9:00.
Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday will be normal (8:00 am).

We are going to start opening the weight room Tuesday and Thursday evening for the kids that are unable to make the morning workouts. Do not use this as an excuse to sleep in! You are going to benefit more from the morning session. We do more agilities and sport specific.

As of right now we do not have to wear a mask to workouts. Our county does not have enough active cases. We will continue to monitor the situation and keep you updated.

post_text:
Thank you so much to Eddie Fenoglio Jr. for his time volunteering to be our fearless leader and President for the last 2 years and membership for years before that. Eddie spent a lot of time in the concessions, lining up cooks, making sure we had all of the equipment needed, and organizing the clubs efforts. Thank you also to Chris Fenoglio for doing so much for our student athletes. She has been the organizer behind Friday lunches, posters getting in business windows, working concessions, and even painting the football field emblem!
Please express your gratitude to the Fenoglio’s when you see them!!

Thank you to Sherre DeLoach Horn for serving as a member of the booster club! Sherre has sold ads to our fall program for several years and helped out with all of our endeavors. We will miss seeing Sherre at our meetings!

2020-2021 Nocona Indian Booster Club Officers are as follows:
Steven Nobile - President
Melanie Hansard - Vice President
Andrea Nobile - Treasurer
Tracie Sparkman - Secretary

Be on the lookout next week for scholarship recipients on the sports awards video!

Tonight’s one of those nights that when we are old and grey, we will look back on and remember. One of Coach Spitzer’s big nights. Or, at least, another sweet step in this Coach’s Life. KG officially has 100 wins as a head coach, and I’m so dang proud and thankful to be along for this ride!

We love you, Coach Spitzer!! And we also LOVE the Lady Indians and their heart and hard work!
